.TH "DESKLAUNCH" "1" "2026-05-21"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
desklaunch - launch or inspect a single XDG desktop entry
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBdesklaunch\fR [\fB-p\fR] <path>
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBdesklaunch\fR parses the .\&desktop file at \fIpath\fR, extracts the \fIExec=\fR
line, strips field codes per the Desktop Entry specification, and starts
the command in the background.\&
.PP
With the \fB-p\fR flag the command is printed to stdout instead of executed.\&
.PP
Both modes update the launch history file so that \fBlsdesktop\fR(1) ordering
stays current.\&
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
\fB-p\fR
.RS 4
.PD
.RE
Print the cleaned exec command to stdout without running it.\&
.PP
.SH FILES
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
\fI$HOME/.\&cache/lsdesktop/history\fR
.RS 4
.PD
.RE
Launch history.\&  Updated by \fBdesklaunch\fR, read by \fBlsdesktop\fR(1).\&
.PP
.SH EXIT STATUS
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
0
.RS 4
.PD
.RE
Successful execution.\&
.PP
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
1
.RS 4
.PD
.RE
Usage error, missing argument, or command failure.\&
.PP
